<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-05-31T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-05-31T16:00:00-05:00" n="476" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d476">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">195.2/2701: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Vice Consul in Chargé at Canton</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Price</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-05-31T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">May 31,
                                        1921—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your May 26, 3 p.m.</p>
                        <p>Department perceives no objection to Chinese vessels chartered to
                            American Companies flying American flag at mast head. This procedure
                            will not impose additional duties upon American Government beyond
                            protection interests American charterers.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>